title: Design a spiritually evocative, powerful logo for a new spiritual soul coaching business
description:
My coaching business is meant to support individuals 1:1 in their personal development and spiritual journeys. I specifically want to work with them for deep, transformative positive change - which is why I feel it's very important people know my coaching is going to target working with their souls and core - not just superficial parts of their lives.
I want to help anyone who is ready to deeply face and embody their emotions and also bring in positive, huge changes to their lives to live more happily and live in a more fulfilled way.
I also believe I can effectively support people who are children of first generation immigrants and struggle with perfectionism, anxiety, and survivalist tendencies, as well as East Asian clients who may find it challenging to navigate their world as a third culture kid.
other_notes:
I'd really like this logo to be clean (I am not looking for a super intricate, detailed, complex logo - I'd like it to be something that feels easy to understand and relate to), and I believe a circular feel will be important (e.g., image centered inside a circle, a circle logo that has text in between an outer and inner ring [attached some example circular logos]). I also attached a very rough sketch of a basic idea of what I think my logo should look like.
If possible, I'd appreciate musical imagery given the name of my business. However, most important to me image-wise is having a bird image. Specifically, I would like a hummingbird with phoenix influences/colors - or some bird that looks like a combination of a hummingbird and phoenix. My Chinese heritage is important to me, and phoenixes are important symbols in Chinese culture. I don't want the logo to be too busy, which is why if there's not a simple way to incorporate musical imagery with the bird image, it's ok to leave it out - however, of course, if there's a way to incorporate the music with the bird image that's still clean, I would appreciate that.
While I am open to different colors in the logo, the phoenix is usually associated with fire, and fire is an important element to me personally - so that is why I have a feeling red, or multiple shades of red, may be important in the logo.
I'd love for the feel of the logo to reflect that my coaching is meant to touch people's souls and help them sing their soul's song.
